{"code": "# Now let's examine the events more carefully to search for Gavin
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

# First, let's see what the current date/time context is
# We need to define "this week" - let's assume current week
today = datetime.now()
week_start = today - timedelta(days=today.weekday())  # Monday of this week
week_end = week_start + timedelta(days=6)  # Sunday of this week

print(f"Searching for meetings with Gavin from {week_start.date()} to {week_end.date()}")

gavin_meetings = []

for i, event in enumerate(calendar._events):
    print(f"Checking event {i}: {event.title if hasattr(event, 'title') else 'No title'}")
    
    # Check if Gavin is mentioned in participants, title, or description
    gavin_found = False
    event_details = ""
    
    if hasattr(event, 'participants') and event.participants:
        participants_str = str(event.participants).lower()
        if 'gavin' in participants_str:
            gavin_found = True
            event_details += f"Participants: {event.participants}"
    
    if hasattr(event, 'title') and event.title and 'gavin' in str(event.title).lower():
        gavin_found = True
        event_details += f"Title: {event.title}"
    
    if hasattr(event, 'description') and event.description and 'gavin' in str(event.description).lower():
        gavin_found = True
        event_details += f"Description: {event.description}"
    
    if gavin_found:
        # Check if it's this week - for now let's assume all events are relevant since we don't have clear date info
        gavin_meetings.append({
            'title': getattr(event, 'title', 'No title'),
            'start_time': getattr(event, 'start_time', 'No start time'),
            'participants': getattr(event, 'participants', []),
            'description': getattr(event, 'description', '')
        })
        print(f"  Found Gavin meeting: {event.title}")

print(f"Found {len(gavin_meetings)} meetings with Gavin")"}

{"code": "# Let me see the current day context to understand what "next Thursday" means
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

# First let's see what calendar_start refers to
print(f"calendar_start: {calendar_start}")
print(f"calendar_start type: {type(calendar_start)}")

# Check if there are any Thursday scrum events
import datetime as dt
for i, event in enumerate(calendar._events):
    if 'scrum' in event.description.lower():
        # Parse the start time to check if it's Thursday
        start_dt = dt.datetime.fromisoformat(event.start_time.replace('Z', '+00:00'))
        day_of_week = start_dt.weekday()  # Monday=0, Tuesday=1, ..., Sunday=6
        print(f"Event {i} ({event.description}) is on day {day_of_week} (Thursday=3)")
        if day_of_week == 3:  # Thursday
            print(f"  This is the Thursday scrum event: {event.description}")
            print(f"  Current participants: {event.participants}")
            print(f"  Event ID: {event.id}")"}
